[2] Worldwide update - Polio Eradication Initiative
Date: 24 Aug 2011
Source: Polio eradication initiative
http://www.polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring/Poliothisweek.aspx

Polio this week - As of Wednesday 24 August 2011

One 3rd (111) of all polio cases reported so far this year (333) have
occurred in endemic countries while 2 3rds (222) have taken place in
re-established or importation countries. Over 50 percent (175) of all
cases come from just 2 countries: Chad and the Democratic Republic of
the Congo.

Wild poliovirus (WPV) cases
----------------------
Data in WHO as of 24 Aug 2010 for 2010 data and 23 Aug 2011 for 2011
data.

*The 2010 total for Congo includes cases with inadequate specimens
that have been exceptionally classified as confirmed polio based on
their association with the WPV1 outbreak.

Afghanistan
- One new case was reported in the past week. The total number of
cases for 2011 is now 13. The most recent case (wild poliovirus type 1
- WPV1) had onset of paralysis [2 Aug 2011] in Kandahar district in
Kandahar province.
- The latest Supplementary Immunization Activities (SIAs) performed
were Sub-national Immunization Days (SNIDs) held from [10-12 Jul
2011]. Bivalent oral polio vaccine (bOPV) was used to vaccinate
children in high risk districts. The next SIAs will be National
Immunization Days (NIDs) from [12-14 Sep 2011] using trivalent oral
polio vaccine (tOPV). A further round of NIDs is planned for [24-26
Oct 2011] using bOPV.

India
- India has not reported a single case in more than 7 months. The most
recent case had onset of paralysis on 13 January in West Bengal
(WPV1).
- The most recent SIAs were SNIDs held from [26 Jun 2011]. SNIDs using
bOPV will be held from [21 Aug 2011] in parts of Uttar Pradesh, Bihar
(starts [28 Aug 2011]), West Bengal and other high-risk areas.
- Preparations are under way for a mucosal immunity study in
Moradabad, with the aim to start on [5 Sep 2011].
- Serosurveys were completed in high risk blocks of Uttar Pradesh and
Bihar in the beginning of August [2011]. Samples have been sent to the
Mumbai Enterovirus Research Centre laboratory for testing.

Nigeria
- Two new cases were officially reported in the past week. The total
number of cases reported from Nigeria in 2011 has increased to 25.The
most recent case is from the newly infected Local Government Area
(LGA) of Bagudo, Kebbi State, with onset of paralysis recorded on [20
Jul 2011].
- All cases in Nigeria have been covered by at least 2 rounds of
supplementary immunization except this latest case in Kebbi, which has
been covered by just one round.
- An additional WPV1 is the 4th WPV1 reported from Kumbotso LGA this
year.
- Preparations are under way for the 7th large scale SIA in Nigeria in
2011 which will cover 15 states and the Federal Capital Territory
(FCT). The round is scheduled for [24-27 Sep 2011] using bOPV.

Pakistan
- Three new cases (all WPV1) were reported this week. The total number
of cases for 2011 is now 72 (71 WPV1 cases and one WPV3 case). The
most recent case (WPV1) had onset of paralysis on [7 Aug 2011] in
Pishin district of Balochistan.
- The 2nd of 2 Short Interval Additional Dose (SIAD) rounds was
conducted in the high risk union councils of 5 districts of
Balochistan from [22 Aug 2011]. The 1st passage took place from [17-19
Aug 2011].
- The latest SIAs performed were NIDs using bOPV on [18-20 Jul 2011].
The next scheduled rounds will be SNIDs using bOPV from [19-21 Sep
2011].
- Aga Khan University is organizing a Polio Workshop on [28-29 Aug
2011] to share findings from seroprevalence and zinc/OPV studies.


Angola
- No new cases were reported in the past week. The total number of
cases for 2011 remains 4. The most recent case (WPV1) had onset of
paralysis on [27 Mar 2011] in Kuando Kubango.
- The most recent SIAs were SNIDs using bOPV, held from [8-10 Jul
2011], in Luanda, Kuando Kubango, Cunene and 3 municipalities of Uige.
The next SIAs will be Child Health Days (CHDs) to be held on [9-22 Sep
2011]. Trivalent OPV will be distributed to children under 5 along
with measles vaccine, vitamin A and deworming tablets.


Chad
- No new cases were reported in the past week. The total number of
cases for 2011 is 100 (97 WPV1, 3 WPV3). The most recent case (WPV1)
had onset of paralysis on [16 Jul 2011] in Benoye, Logone Occidental.
- The latest 'staggered' immunization round which commenced [29 Jul
2011] using bOPV have been completed. The next round is scheduled for
September [2011].

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC)
- Two new cases were reported in the past week. The total number of
cases for 2011 is now 75 (all WPV1). The most recent case had onset of
paralysis on [25 Jul 2011] in Kimvula, Bas-Congo.
- SNIDs using monovalent OPV type 1 (mOPV1) are planned for [25-27 Aug
2011] in Kimvula, Popokabaka and Ankoro. A further round of SNIDs is
planned for [8-10 Sep 2011].

Horn of Africa
- No wild polio virus cases have been reported from this group of
countries this year.
- The security situation in the greater Mogadishu area, Somalia,
remains fluid - GPEI local staff is closely watching the situation for
any opportunity to rapidly improve the immunity of the children of
Mogadishu.
- A 1st round of Child Heath Days (CHDs) using tOPV were performed in
parts of Somalia in July [2011] (Somaliland [12-16 Jul 2011], Puntland
[18-21 Jul 2011]). 'Staggered' CHDs commenced on [18 Aug 2011] in
Banadir. A 2nd round is scheduled from [4-8 Dec 2011].
- SNIDs using bOPV will be held in the Darfur provinces from [26 Sep
2011] to protect against spread from neighbouring Chad. Northern Sudan
has NIDs using bOPV planned for [14-16 Nov 2011] and further NIDs
using tOPV planned for [12-14 Dec 2011].
- Southern Sudan has NIDs using tOPV planned for [1-4 Nov 2011].
Another round of NIDs, this time using bOPV, is planned for [6-8 Dec
2011].
- Egypt is planning self-funded SIAs for October [2011].

West Africa
- One new case was reported from this region in the past week (WPV3 in
Guinea). The total number of cases for 2011 in the West Africa region
is now 41 (all WPV3s - 2 from Burkina Faso, 31 from Cote d'Ivoire, 2
from Guinea, 5 from Mali and one from Niger). The most recent case
(WPV3) had onset of paralysis on [27 Jul 2011] in Siguiri district of
Kankan province, Guinea.
- Cote d'Ivoire accounts for by far the largest number of WPV3 cases
reported this year, with a total of 31. No other country has reported
double-digit WPV3 case numbers.
- Cote d'Ivoire and 6 neighbouring countries held a multi-country
round from [18 Aug 2011]. A combination of bOPV and mOPV 3 was used to
help combat the outbreak of WPV3. SNIDs using mOPV3 were held in
Burkina Faso, Ghana, Guinea, Liberia and Mali. NIDs using mOPV3 took
place in Sierra Leone. CÃ´te d'Ivoire held NIDs on [19 Aug 2011] using
bOPV.
- Further, large-scale, multi-country rounds are being planned for
much of west Africa for September and October [2011].


[The occurrence of 4 cases of wild poliovirus (WPV) associated disease
in Xinjiang Autonomous Region of Western China with a genetic
sequencing identifying the viruses as the same as those circulating in
Pakistan in 2009 suggests that there has most likely been "silent"
transmission of these viruses in either Pakistan or Xinjiang
Autonomous Region for the past 2 years. Unfortunately the continued
circulation of WPV in areas with suboptimal programmatic activities
due to infrastructural challenges and/or civil unrest has been posing
the most significant challenges to the goal of eradication of the
WPV.

A map showing the geographic locations of WPV associated paralytic
cases as of 24 Aug 2011 can be found at
http://www.polioeradication.org/Dataandmonitoring.aspx.]
